# React Patterns — iframe-app

- Functional components only, one exported component per file.
- Any data-fetching or mutation logic goes in a hook under `src/hooks/`
  (see `data-fetching.mdc`) — components render, hooks fetch.
- RPC method handlers passed to `useRpcBridge` must stay thin (see
  `json-rpc-protocol.mdc`).
- Prefer composing from `@parceliq/ui` primitives over writing new markup.
- Effects that depend on an object/array prop (like `theme`) must get that
  value from a memoized source upstream — an inline object literal in a
  parent's render body will change identity every render and can cause an
  effect to fire in a loop. (This exact bug happened once with `setTheme` —
  don't reintroduce it.)
